ida-adreno-qrisc
================

This project includes ISA and PM4 packet definitions generated from the Mesa
3D Graphics Library:

  https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/mesa/mesa

Specifically, the following Mesa files are used at generation time to produce
the standalone decode tables in `common/qrisc_isa_tables.py`:

  src/freedreno/qrisc/qrisc.xml
  src/freedreno/registers/adreno/adreno_control_regs.xml
  src/freedreno/registers/adreno/adreno_pm4.xml

These files are licensed under the MIT License and copyright their respective
authors (Google, Inc.; Valve Corporation; Rob Clark; and other Mesa
contributors), per the Mesa repository.

The generator (`gen/qrisc_isa_gen.py`) re-uses Mesa's own `isa.py` parser
(`src/compiler/isaspec/isa.py`, MIT, copyright Google) at generation time. No
Mesa code or data is required at runtime — the generated tables are pure
data and ship as part of this project.

Pinned Mesa commit at the time of release:
  4bf8fd5121122abd87aafb31e43bbbe9e3d2e921 (Mesa main, 2026-06-22)

The license-clean test fixtures `fixtures/qrisc_test*.fw` and
`fixtures/qrisc_test*.asm` are reproduced from Mesa's `src/freedreno/tests/`
and remain under their original license.

